article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 69, Jarvis Christian 46
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Matt Kingsley scored 19 points to lead Stephen F. Austin to a 69-46 win over Jarvis Christian on Saturday night. Kingsley hit 9-of-12 shots from the field and grabbed seven rebounds for the Lumberjacks (8-4). Benson Akpan added 11 points on 5-of-6 shooting. David Greene scored eight points to lead Jarvis Christian (8-2), an NAIA school that played the game as an exhibition. Jarvis Christian hit just 22 percent of its shots from the field, including 3-of-15 attempts from beyond the 3-point arc. Stephen F. Austin led 35-22 at the half.
